---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '../components/Breadcrumbs.astro';
import PageHero from '../components/PageHero.astro';
import { SITE } from '../config';

const path = '/terms';
const title = 'Terms and TCPA Disclosures';
const description =
  'The terms of use for Lilac City ADU and the TCPA consent and contact disclosures that apply to the get-matched form.';
const effective = 'June 2026';
---
<BaseLayout title={title} description={description} path={path}>
  <Breadcrumbs items={[{ label: 'Terms and TCPA', href: path }]} />
  <PageHero eyebrow="Legal" title="Terms and TCPA disclosures" lede={`Effective ${effective}. These terms govern your use of ${SITE.name} and explain the consent that applies when you contact us.`} />

  <section class="container-prose rich-text pb-10">
    <p class="text-sm text-basalt-soft">
      This is a general template provided for transparency. The operator should have it reviewed by
      qualified counsel before promotion.
    </p>

    <h2>About the service</h2>
    <p>
      {SITE.name} is operated by {SITE.entityLegal}, doing business as {SITE.entityDba}. We are a
      marketing and matching service that connects homeowners with independent licensed local ADU
      builders. We do not design, permit, or build, and we are not a contractor, architect, engineer,
      or lender. All construction is performed by independent licensed third-party builders that you
      contract with directly.
    </p>

    <h2>No professional advice and no guarantees</h2>
    <p>
      Content on this site is general information, not legal, financial, or construction advice. We do
      not guarantee any price, timeline, financing approval, permit outcome, or the work of any
      builder. Regulatory and cost details should be confirmed with the relevant jurisdiction and a
      licensed professional before you act.
    </p>

    <h2>Independent builders</h2>
    <p>
      The builder you are matched with is an independent business. We are not responsible for their
      work, contracts, or conduct. Your agreement for design, permitting, and construction is between
      you and that builder.
    </p>

    <h2>Acceptable use</h2>
    <p>You agree to provide accurate information and to use the site lawfully and only for your own ADU project research.</p>

    <h2>Intellectual property</h2>
    <p>The site content and brand are owned by {SITE.entityLegal}. You may not copy or reuse it without permission.</p>

    <h2>Limitation of liability</h2>
    <p>
      To the fullest extent permitted by law, {SITE.entityLegal} is not liable for indirect,
      incidental, or consequential damages arising from your use of the site or from any builder you
      are matched with.
    </p>

    <h2>Governing law</h2>
    <p>These terms are governed by the laws of the State of Washington.</p>

    <h2>TCPA consent and contact disclosures</h2>
    <p>
      When you submit the get-matched form and check the consent box, you agree that {SITE.entityDba}
      and the licensed local builder you are matched with may contact you about your ADU project. The
      following disclosures apply:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>You consent to be contacted by phone call, text message, and email at the number and address you provide.</li>
      <li>Contact may be made using automated technology where applicable.</li>
      <li>Consent is not a condition of any purchase.</li>
      <li>Message and data rates may apply, and message frequency may vary.</li>
      <li>You can opt out at any time by replying STOP to a text, unsubscribing from an email, or asking us to stop contacting you.</li>
      <li>The consent checkbox is never pre-checked. Submitting without checking it means you have not provided consent to be contacted by those methods.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Changes to these terms</h2>
    <p>We may update these terms. The effective date above reflects the latest version.</p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
      {SITE.entityLegal} doing business as {SITE.entityDba}.<br />
      Operating address: {SITE.addressPlaceholder}<br />
      Email: {SITE.emailPlaceholder}<br />
      Phone: {SITE.phonePlaceholder}
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
